Layer.Name: Foundation.BNDTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Boundaries Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Boundaries Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific boundaries coverage feature or as an attribute of a boundaries coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.COASTL_1M
Layer.Title: Coastlines
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Coastlines":

Coastline/shorelines (BA010) have been portrayed for coastal islands but not inland islands.

Layer.Name: Foundation.DEPTHL_1M
Layer.Title: Depth Contours
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Depth Contours":

Depth contours (BE015) were derived from digital bathymetric data provided by Defense Mapping Agency. Depths are expressed in the following intervals: 200, 600, 1000. 2000, 4000, 6000, and 8000 meters.

Layer.Name: Foundation.OCEANSEA_1M
Layer.Title: Oceans/Seas
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Oceans/Seas":

In coastal area, points of change from ocean/sea areas (BA040) to inland water areas (BH000) were taken from Digital Chart of the World, edition 1, July 1992.

Layer.Name: Foundation.DQTXT_DQ_1M
Layer.Title: Data Quality Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Data Quality Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific data quality coverage feature or as an attribute of a data quality coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.ETOPO2
Layer.Title: Global 2 Minute Elevations
Layer.Abstract: ETOPO2 was generated from a digital data base of land and sea-floor elevations on a 2-minute latitude/longitude grid. The data sources used to create the ETOPO2 data set were: Smith/Sandwell, GLOBE, DBDBV, IBCAO, and DBDB5

Layer.Name: Foundation.GTOPO30
Layer.Title: Global 30 Second Elevations
Layer.Abstract: GTOPO30 is a global digital elevation model (DEM) resulting from a collaborative effort led by the staff at the U.S. Geological Survey's EROS Data Center in Sioux Falls, South Dakota. Elevations in GTOPO30 are regularly spaced at 30-arc seconds (approximately 1 kilometer). GTOPO30 was developed to meet the needs of the geospatial data user community for regional and continental scale topographic data.

Layer.Name: Foundation.CONTOURL_1M
Layer.Title: Elevation Contours
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Elevation Contours":

All elevation contour line height values were converted from feet (as expressed in Digital Chart of the World) to meters.

Layer.Name: Foundation.ELEVP_1M
Layer.Title: Spot Elevations
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Spot Elevations":

Point elevation features (those formed by coalescence of small contour tops, as opposed to conventional spot elevations) from Digital Chart of the World were portrayed as VMAP-0 spot elevations (CA030) with approximate (horizontal) accuracies. All elevation height values were converted from feet (as expressed in Digital Chart of the World) to meters.

Layer.Name: Foundation.HYDROTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Hydrography Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Hydrography Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific hydrography coverage feature or as an attribute of a hydrography coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.INWATERA_1M
Layer.Title: Inland Water Areas
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Inland Water Areas":

In coastal area, points of change from ocean/sea areas (BA040) to inland water areas (BH000) were taken from Digital Chart of the World, edition 1, July 1992 except when it was determined that the point of change was implemented too far inland. In these cases, cartographic judgment was used to establish the point of change.

Layer.Name: Foundation.MISCP_HYDRO_1M
Layer.Title: Miscellaneous Point Features
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Miscellaneous Point Features":

The names for islands has been placed as the Name attribute for polbndp.pft and polbnda.aft when the name appeared on the ONC litho.

Layer.Name: Foundation.INDTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Industry Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Industry Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific industry coverage feature or as an attribute of an industry coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.LANDICEA_1M
Layer.Title: Snow/Ice Fields and Glaciers
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Snow/Ice Fields and Glaciers":

All land ice areas, snow/ice fields, glaciers and snowcaps are included in this feature code (BJ100).

Layer.Name: Foundation.PHYSTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Physiography Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Physiography Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific physiography coverage feature or as an attribute of a physiography coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.BUILTUPP_1M
Layer.Title: Built-Up Area Points
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Built-Up Area Points":

This feature class, which contains built-up area point features (AL020), is comprised of features that were classified as 'populated places associated with place names in city tints' in Digital Chart of the World, edition 1, July 1992.

Layer.Name: Foundation.MISPOPP_1M
Layer.Title: Miscellaneous Population Points
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Miscellaneous Population Points":

The following conversion was implemented to classify area population features from Digital Chart of the World, edition 1, July 1992. 1) DCW point populated places and villages were converted to point settlements (AL105). The name of the city has been placed in the Text attribute (TXT). 2) DCW point "kampongs" and circular villages were converted to native settlement (AL135).

Layer.Name: Foundation.POPTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Population Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Population Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific population coverage feature or as an attribute of a population coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.AEROFACP_1M
Layer.Title: Airport Facilities Points
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Airport Facilities Points":

Information on airports/airfields (GB005) was derived from the DAFIF (Digital Aeronautical Flight Information File) and TINT (Target Intelligence) in areas where such data was available. Each airfield's DAFIF reference number was placed in the 'na3' (classification name) attribute field. Only airfields which had at least one hard surface runway longer that 3,000 feet (910 meters) were collected.

Layer.Name: Foundation.MISTRANL_1M
Layer.Title: Miscellaneous Transportation Line Features
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Miscellaneous Transportation Line Features":

The features within this miscellaneous transportation line feature class - aerial cableway lines/ski lift lines (AQ010) and piers/wharfs/quays (BB190) - were extracted from the cultural landmark layer of Digital Chart of the World, edition1, July 1992. Neither of these features carries any additional attribute information.

Layer.Name: Foundation.ROADL_1M
Layer.Title: Roads
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Roads":

The majority of data contained within the road line feature class was derived from the roads layer of Digital Chart of the World, edition 1, July 1992. All schematic road connectors added in urbanized areas for network connectivity were given an 'exs' (Existence Category attribute) value of '55' (Unexamined/ Unsurveyed). Where possible, road features were designated as primary or secondary routes by comparison with Operational Navigation Charts (ONC) map sources.

Layer.Name: Foundation.TRANSTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Transportation Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Transportation Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific transportation coverage feature or as an attribute of a transportation coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.UTILTXT_1M
Layer.Title: Utilities Coverage Text
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Utilities Coverage Text":

Text features were used to convey information which could not be expressed as a more specific utilities coverage feature or as an attribute of a utilities coverage feature.

Layer.Name: Foundation.TREESA_1M
Layer.Title: Trees
Layer.Abstract:
VRF Narrative Table for "Trees":

This feature class includes all area forest/trees (EC030). Wooded areas are attributed as to predominant tree type (deciduous, evergreen, mixed or other) where possible. All features carrying the veg=999 (Other) attribute are "transitional" forests.

Layer.Name: MapAnnotations.graticule
Layer.Title: Lat/Lon Graticule
Layer.Abstract: Produces graticule lines every 10 degrees of latitude and longitude. If the STYLE for this layer is set to a number, the graticule lines will be spaced that many degrees apart. A STYLE of the form "number:number" is also accepted, specifying the longitudinal and latitudinal spacing separately.

Layer.Name: MapAnnotations.crosshairs
Layer.Title: Crosshairs
Layer.Abstract: Displays a set of crosshairs to indicate the center of the image.

Layer.Name: MapAnnotations.blank
Layer.Title: Blank
Layer.Abstract: Produces a blank image.
